    {
      "id": "eq_7146",
      "raw": "For SU(3), the convex hull has 6 vertices (Weyl orbit), or 3 if p=0 or q=0.",
      "type": "comment",
      "context": "The simplest correct check: enumerate ALL integer points (m1, m2) on the root lattice translated to (p,q), and keep those in the convex hull.",
